<p>For a Great Dane, this is the section that matters most — because of every breed we cover, the giant pup is where a <strong>size-specific food earns its place most clearly</strong>. The whole challenge of feeding a Dane is controlling growth and protecting joints, and that's precisely what a large/giant-breed puppy food is engineered to do.</p>

