<p>Across all of it, three rules matter most for a Great Dane: <strong>keep growth slow and the pup lean</strong> — controlled calcium and energy, body condition ~4/9, never chubby, because over-fast growth is what damages a giant skeleton; <strong>get the calcium balance right and never supplement it</strong> — a large/giant-breed growth food with the right Ca:P ratio does the work; and <strong>feed bloat-safe and be patient</strong> — 2–3 smaller meals, calm after eating, and a long two-year puppyhood before adult food. Any swollen, hard tummy with unproductive retching and distress in a Dane is a same-day, same-hour emergency — bloat can be fatal within hours.</p>

